      <processinfo id="aspace_f7a2a8fc23b382ce7e9e775b1a592ca0">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_c6229518b25204b90d589ba4bba055c6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of the lecture notes, examinations, syllabi and handouts documenting Ivan Phillips's undergraduate courses taken between 1952-1956, including courses in history, economics, and science. Also included are several grade school notebooks.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_052cd18415b5dcbc9e686977bbe8d939">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The papers are arranged chronologically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_c490dfb9293b53eafaff2fec29d29297">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Ivan Edward Phillips was born to Lazarus and Rosalie Idelson Phillips on May 10, 1934 in Montreal, Quebec. He prepared at the Selwyn House School in Montreal and at Deerfield before entering Yale in 1952. He graduated in 1956 as a history major. He was a member of Silliman College and Chi Psi Fraternity as well as a member of the Record Board from 1953-1955.</p>  
      </bioghist>
